    <td valign=3D"top" bgcolor=3D"#FFFFFF" class=3D"PageText11"><p class=3D=
"wordHeadings2">standard form</p>
      <p class=3D"PageText11">=E2=80=A2 standard form has two definitions,<=
br>
      each depending on which country you are in.</p>
      <p class=3D"PageText11"><span class=3D"wordHeadings2">United Kingdom =
and countries using UK conventions</span><br>
        =E2=80=A2 standard form is another name for scientific notation,<br=
>
      i.e. 876 =3D 8.76 x 10<sup>2</sup>.</p>
      <p class=3D"PageText11"><span class=3D"wordHeadings2">United States a=
nd countries using US conventions</span><br>
        =E2=80=A2 standard form is the usual way of writing numbers in deci=
mal notation, i.e.<br>
        standard form =3D 876, expanded form =3D 800 + 70 + 6,<br>
        written form =3D eight hundred seventy six.
  <br>
      </p>
      <p class=3D"PageText11">EXAMPLES:<br>
